==English==

=== Etymology ===
[[Category:Disputed etymologies]] Derived from ''[[borken]]'', which is an intentional misspelling of the word ''broken''.  ''The computer is borken''.  The word is often used in ironic or humorous contexts.

===Pronunciation===
*/b…îrk/, /bOrk/

=== Verb ===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|bork||}}
# To misconfigure, especially a computer or other complex device.
# To break or damage.
# To snub or disrespect.